RECOMMENDED CONTROL: linear
  valid controls ranked by movement removed (most first): linear, pca, ridge
  at the realistic rho (0.532) a threshold signal recovers to AUC 0.568 through this control

why each rejected or sub-optimal control is not recommended for this data:
  - ridge: valid, but removes less movement than linear (remove-test AUC 0.540 vs 0.508), can under-remove low-variance confound, so linear is preferred.
  - pca: valid, but removes less movement than linear (remove-test AUC 0.529 vs 0.508), can under-remove low-variance confound, so linear is preferred.
  - expanded: FAILS preserve test, retains 48 percent of a movement-orthogonal signal, over-corrects by overfitting at this trial count.
  - crossfit: FAILS preserve test, retains -18 percent of a movement-orthogonal signal, over-corrects by overfitting at this trial count.

